author: Scott Piker
title: Cleveland Browns inactives vs. St. Louis
text:
Photo by Jeff Gross/Getty Images Once again the Cleveland Browns will be without some key members of the defense in week seven as they face the St. Louis Rams. Here are the Browns inactive players for Sunday's game in St. Louis.
QB Austin Davis
DB Joe Haden
DB Tashaun Gipson
LB Craig Robertson
WR Dwayne Bowe
TE Rob Housler
TE E.J. Bibbs
Haden remains in the NFL's protocol for concussions for a second straight week. Gipson and Robertson continue to deal with ankle injuries. DB Pierre Desir will start for Haden at cornerback. Housler suffered a hamstring injury last week against Denver.
